@NODE WhatIs "TConf: What IS it?"

	TConf Is Quite Simply A Conference Access Lister Door. I Know Your
Thinking That The Two or Three Already In Exsistence Are Slow So How The
Hell Can This Be A Door? Well, TConf Can Update In REALTIME in Under A
Second Due To It Being Written Entirely In Assembler. Try It Once And You'll
Throw Away The Others For Good! Just Take A Look At Some Of The @{"Features"Link Features}.
TConf Is Compatable With All Versions Of Ami-Express Including S-Express By 
Sigma-Seven.

        A Quick Note To Chart-Loosers. If Your Gonna Vote On Any Sad,
Fake,Fixed Charts, At Least Make Sure You Get It Right!. Dont Vote For
Either Myself Or P0T-N00dle As Individuals. We BOTH Do all The Work -
Take A Look At The @{"Releases" LINK Others} We Have Both Done For You
All So Far!. Please Vote For Us As:

                          GODS'GIFT/ANTHROX

PS: If Somebody Else Asks P0T-N00Dle About "HIS" Tbar/TTop Etc, Ill Blow
    A Fuckin Fuse! HeHe.
@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE Features "TConf: Features"

     o - The GodsGift Seal Of Quality (Even More Rigorous Than Nintendo!)
     o - 100% Assembly Language (As Always!).
     o - 32 Node Compatable.(Actually 100!).
     o - Compatable With ALL versions And Variants Of Ami-Express.
     o - Can Be Run Resident.
     o - RealTime Update Cause You Aint Never Seen One THIS Fast Before!
     o - Using Nice And Easy Icon ToolTypes For ALL Command Options.
     o - Can Display ANY Mixture Of conferences/Access "AREAS".
     o - Optional HeaderFile Display.
     o - Optional TailerFile Display.
     o - Optional Statistics Bar.
     o - Optional ClearScreen For Faster Ansi Displays & lazy Sysops.
     o - Optional Password Protection (With Failure Comments To Callerslog).
     o - Configurable Password Attempts.
     o - One-Time-Passwords!!! (This one Is NICE for The Users!)
     o - Fluffy Sheep Jumping On Pink Clouds All Over The Place.
     o - I Was 100% Sober ThroughOut ALL coding.. (Well Almost!)
     o - Not One Mention Of Fish-Fingers (SHIT!)
     o - These Are Getting Silly.
@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE Installing "TConf: Installation"





Which Version Of Expess Are You Running?


         @{" Version 2.x +/Variant " Link InstallingV2}  ........ Non-Icon Versions
         @{" Version 3.x +/Variant " Link InstallingV3}  ........ Icon/ToolType Versions

@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE InstallingV3 "TConf: Installation Express V3.x+"
Make An Icon In Your Commands/BBSCMD (Or Commands/ConfX) Directory With
The Following ToolTypes:

LOCATION=Path And Name Of This Util (Ie DOORS:TCONF2)
MULTINODE=YES
TYPE=XIM
STACK=4096

Now Make An Icon (One Is Supplied In This Archive) For TConf2 Itself. You
Can Rename The Util To Whatever You Wish So You Can Run Multiple Versions
For Different Conferences/Areas. Just Remember To Make The Icons For EVERY
Copy You Want To Use. All Options Are Controlled By The Doors Icon 
@{"ToolTypes"Link ToolTypes} For Ease Of Use For Users Of Ami-Express V3+.
An Example Icon Is Supplied WIthin This Archive.
@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE InstallingV2 "TConf: Installation Express V2.x+ / Variant"

Copy The Main Executable File To Your Doors Directory Or WhereEver You Want
it. Make An Icon For The Util To Get Its Options From The @{"ToolTypes"Link ToolTypes}.

You Can Rename The Util To Whatever You Wish So You Can Run Multiple
Versions For Different Conferences/Areas. Just Remember To Make An Icon And
An EXE For EVERY Different Copy You Want To Use. An Example Icon Is Supplied
WIthin This Archive.


@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-



@NODE ToolTypes "TConf: Icon ToolTypes"

These Are All The ToolTypes Available To The Sysop:


            @{" USER_DATA= " Link USER_DATA}  ........ Full Path/Name Of UserData.
            @{" ACCESS_AREAS= " Link ACCESS_AREAS} ...... Area Names / Conference Numbers.
            @{" HEADER_TEXT= " Link HEADER_TEXT} ....... Header Text To Be Displayed.
            @{" TAILER_TEXT= " Link TAILER_TEXT} ....... Bottom Text To Be Displayed.
            @{" CLEAR_SCREEN= " Link CLEAR_SCREEN} ...... Clear Sceen Before Any Output.
            @{" STATS_BAR= " Link STATS_BAR} ......... Small Stats Bar Underneath Users.
            @{" CONF_NAME= " Link CONF_NAME} ......... Name Of Conference To Be Displayed.
            @{" PASSWORD= " Link PASSWORD} .......... Password Required To Continue.
            @{" PASSWORD_TRIES= " Link PASSWORD_TRIES} .... Allowed Password Attempts.
            @{" HACK_TEXT= " Link HACK_TEXT} ......... HangUp Text To Be Displayed.
            @{" ONE_TIME_PASSWORD= " Link ONE_TIME_PASSWORD} . Special Type Of PassWord.
            @{" EXPRESS_VERSION= " Link VERSION} ... Version/Variant Number Of Ami-Express.
@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE USER_DATA "TConf: ToolTypes - USER_DATA"

USER_DATA=X

This ToolType MUST Exist. "X" Is Simply The FULL Path AND Name Of Your
UserData File ie:

USER_DATA=BBS:USER.DATA
@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE ACCESS_AREAS "TConf: ToolTypes - ACCESS_AREAS"


Which Version Of Expess Are You Running?


         @{" Version 2.x +/Variant " Link ACCESS_AREAS_V2}  ........ Non-Icon Versions
         @{" Version 3.x +/Variant " Link ACCESS_AREAS_V3}  ........ Icon/ToolType Versions
@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE ACCESS_AREAS_V3 "TConf: ToolTypes - ACCESS_AREAS /X3+"

ACCESS_AREAS=AREANAME1;AREANAME2 Etc..

This Is The Name Of The Area Used In Your "Access" Drawer. Multiple Areas
Can Be Used But Each Area MUST Be Seperated By a Semi-Colon ";". Ie..

ACCESS_AREAS=SYSOP;NEWUSERS        - Show Users Whose "AREA" Is SYSOP Or
                                     NEWUSERS.

Or

ACCESS_AREAS=SYSOP;SPECIAL_USERS;AMIGA;CONSOLE
@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE ACCESS_AREAS_V2 "TConf: ToolTypes - ACCESS_AREAS /X2+"

ACCESS_AREAS=X;X;X Etc......


Where "X" Is The NUMBER Of the COnference You Want TConf To Display. You
Can Use Multiple Conferences But Each Must Be Seperated By A Semi-Colon (;).
Ie:

ACCESS_AREAS=5          - Show Users With Access To Conf 5.

Or

ACCESS_AREAS=5;9;1      - Show Users With Access To Confs 5;9 And 1.
@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE HEADER_TEXT "TConf: ToolTypes - HEADER_TEXT"

HEADER_TEXT=X

Where "X" Is The FULL Path AND Name Of A Header/Logo Text You Wish To Be 
Displayed BEFORE Any User Information Is Shown.Ie

HEADER_TEXT=BBS:SCREENS/AMIGA/ACCESS_LOGO1.TXT
@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE TAILER_TEXT "TConf: ToolTypes - TAILER_TEXT"

TAILER_TEXT=X

Where "X" Is The FULL Path AND Name Of A Tailer/Logo Text You Wish To Be 
Displayed AFTER Any User Information Has Been Shown.Ie

HEADER_TEXT=BBS:SCREENS/AMIGA/ACCESS_BOTTOM.TXT
@ENDNODE
@NODE CLEAR_SCREEN "TConf: ToolTypes - CLEAR_SCREEN"

CLEAR_SCREEN=YES/NO

If You Wish The Screen To Be Cleared BEFORE Any Text Is Shown Then Make
This YES. It Just Saves Lazy Sysops From Including A Screen Clear On Logos.
And Of Course Will Mean The Screen Update Will Be Slightly Faster Due To
No "Scroll-Up" By Ami-Express.

@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE STATS_BAR "TConf: ToolTypes - STATS_BAR"

STATS_BAR=YES/NO

If You Wish The One Line Of Quick-Stats To Be Displayed At The Bottom Then
Set This To YES. It Will Take The Util NO LONGER To Execute So You May As
Well Leave It In, Unless You Simply Dont Like The Idea.
@ENDNODE
@NODE CONF_NAME "TConf: ToolTypes - CONF_NAME"

CONF_NAME=YES/NO

After The Logo/ClearScreen But BEFORE The Users Are Displayed To The Screen,
You Can Have The Conference Name From Which The Util Was Run Displayed At The
Top Of The Ansi Output. Simply A Yes/No Option. NOTE: I said The Name Of
The Conference TConf Was Run FROM. *NOT* The Conference/s You Have Put Into
The @{" ACCESS_AREAS= " Link ACCESS_AREAS} ToolType.

@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE PASSWORD "TConf: ToolTypes - PASSWORD"

PASSWORD=XXXX....

If TConf Finds This ToolType Present With A Valid Password It Will Ask
The User To Input The Correct Password Before It Will Let Him Exit The
Util And Proceed Within The Conference. This Is Mainly Here For Those
Sysops Who Wish To Run This Door As Soon As A User Has Joined A Private
Conference. The Password Can be ANY combination Of Numbers/Letters Etc,
Upto A Maximum Limit Of 59 Characters. The Check Made Is NOT Case Sensitive
Cause That Only Would Piss Legitimate Users Off! The User Will Be Given
3 Attempts To Enter The Correct Password Followed By Return. If They
Fail All 3 Attempts TConf Will Legally Drop Carrier On The User And Notify
The Sysop By Leaving A Suitable Comment Attached To The Nodes CallersLog.
Ami-Express Will Then Reset The Node And Await The Next Caller.



See Also: 

@{" PASSWORD_TRIES= " Link PASSWORD_TRIES},@{" ONE_TIME_PASSWORD= " Link ONE_TIME_PASSWORD},@{" HACK_TEXT= " Link HACK_TEXT}

@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE PASSWORD_TRIES "TConf: ToolTypes - PASSWORD_TRIES"

PASSWORD_TRIES=X

Where X Is A Number Between 1 And 9. This Tells TConf How Many Attempts
At Getting The Correct PassWord Are Allowed Before The User Is Kicked
Off The Board. If This ToolType Is NOT Found Then TConf Will Default To
3 Attempts If PassWords Are Required.


See Also: 

@{" ONE_TIME_PASSWORD= " Link ONE_TIME_PASSWORD},@{" HACK_TEXT= " Link HACK_TEXT},@{" PASSWORD= " Link PASSWORD}

@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE HACK_TEXT "TConf: ToolTypes - HACK_TEXT"

HACK_TEXT=X

Where X Is The FULL Name And Path Of A Text File The Sysop Wants To Be
Displayed Just Before A User/Hacker Is To Be Kicked Off The BBS. Ie

HACK_TEXT=BBS:DOORS/TCONF/FUCK_OFF.TXT



See Also: 

@{" PASSWORD_TRIES= " Link PASSWORD_TRIES},@{" ONE_TIME_PASSWORD= " Link ONE_TIME_PASSWORD},@{" PASSWORD= " Link PASSWORD}

@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE ONE_TIME_PASSWORD "TConf: ToolTypes - ONE_TIME_PASSWORD"

ONE_TIME_PASSWORD=YES/NO

This Is A Special PassWord Option. In Order For This To Run Correctly
You Will Need To Have An Assigned T: Directory. When A User Logs On
And Correctly Gets The PassWord To A Particular Conference A SMALL File
In Your T: Dieectory Will Be Created By TConf. If He Rejoins This Same
Conf He Will NOT Need To Type In The PassWord Again. TConf Will Keep 
Track Of ALL Conference PassWords Correctly Accessed By The User And 
Not Ask For Them A Second Time. This Even Tracks If The User Uses "RL" 
To Re-Logon Or Simply Calls The Same Node Again Before Any Other Users.

           Although A Good Idea (Thanks T.G.R!), This Way Of Doing
Things Does Have A slight Problem. If A Hacking User Logs OnTo The Board
Straight After The Legitimate User Has Called He Would Have Access
To The Protected Conference (DUMB!!). A Simple Way Of Stopping This 
Problem Is To Delete The File Created In The T: Directory In That 
Particular Nodes Logoff-Script. So Simply Add To Each Nodes Logoff-Script
The Following Line:

DELETE T:TConfUser_NodeX     << "X" Is The Node Of The Logoff-Script!!

This Will Mean The User WOULD Be required To Insert The Correct PassWord
If He Re-Logs On Or Is The Next Person To Call The SAME Node, And Gets
Rid Of The Hacker Problem. I could Have Built This In But It Would Mean
You Would Have To Run A Second Util As Your "G" Or "RL" Commands And
This Was Thought To Be NOT A Good Idea. (Even If "G" Doors Do Suk In My
Books!)

          Its A Little Hard To Explain How It Works So Try It Out And 
See For YourSelf. A Nice Idea, But ,Of Course, Its Only Optional!

   If This ToolType Does NOT Exist, Then TConf Will Default To NO.

See Also: 

@{" PASSWORD_TRIES= " Link PASSWORD_TRIES},@{" HACK_TEXT= " Link HACK_TEXT},@{" PASSWORD= " Link PASSWORD}
@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE VERSION "TConf: ToolTypes - EXPRESS_VERSION"

EXPRESS_VERSION=X

Where "X" Is the MAIN Version Number Of The Express/Express Variant You Are 
Using. TConf Of Course CAN Find The Internal Version By Itself (Which It 
Does By Default If This ToolType Does NOT Exist), However This Will Allow
The Variant Programmers Who Are Using The OLD! Version 2 Release To Upgrade
Their Version To Number To 3 Without This Util Screwing Up On Them. 
Ie If your Version Of Express Uses Icon ToolTypes For Everything Then:

EXPRESS_VERSION=3

EXPRESS_VERSION=4

If,However You Are Using S-Express 3 (If There Ever Is One), But It DOESNT
Use Icon ToolTypes Then You Should Have:

EXPRESS_VERSION=2


Was That Simple Enough For You???.. Now You Can Upgrade The Version Number
Properly Stefan!

@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@NODE RUNNING "TConf: Running From Ami-Express."

You Have Two Choices For Running TConf. Any Sysop Should Know What They Are.
Simply Have The User Type In Whatever You Have Setup For The Door TO Run. Ie
In This Archive They Would Type In "ACCESS" And Be Told What Users Have 
Access To The Confs Desribed In The ToolTypes. Or You Can Set It Up To Run
In An MCI script. For Instance Your NewUsers/Bull100.Txt May Say...

~
~CC_ACCESS

Which In MCI-Script Language Tells Ami-Express To Run The Door Called
ACCESS Rather Than Display This As A text File. Simple Stuff Eh?

Also See Notes On @{"Installation "Link Installing}.
@ENDNODE

@REMARK -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
